======================
SymtabAPI Build Notes
======================

Home: http://www.paradyn.org/
      http://www.dyninst.org/

Download: ftp://ftp.cs.wisc.edu/paradyn/releases/

License: LGPL

Prereqs: boost libdwarf libelf (libxml2 libunwind)

Now uses autoconf but not automake.
Does not support vpath build or parallel make.

export PLATFORM=platform
cd SymtabAPI-8.0

./configure CC=CC CFLAGS=flags CXX=CXX CXXFLAGS=flags  \
    --prefix=prefix  \
    --bindir=bindir  \
    --includedir=includedir  \
    --libdir=libdir  \
    --with-libelf-incdir=incdir  \
    --with-libelf-libdir=libdir  \
    --with-default-component=SymtabAPI  \
    --disable-testsuite  \
    ...
make
make install

Beginning with symtabAPI 8.0, the boost headers are separate and no
longer in the symtab source tree.  For now, they only use boost
headers, no libs.

Symtab configure uses CC, CXX and flags for config tests, but doesn't
fully pass them to make, so we force them into make.config.local.

Some compilers don't support tr1/unordered_map (old module at05 on
biou).  In that case, disable unordered_map in dyntypes.h via a
conditional patch.

